info.headline: Flood Warning issued October 28 at 10:26AM EDT by NWS Melbourne FL
info.description:
...The Flood Warning is extended for the following rivers in Florida...
St Johns River Near Above Lake Harney affecting Seminole County.
.The Saint Johns River above Lake Harney near Geneva is forecast to steadily rise to minor flood stage tonight due to recent heavy rainfall. Once reaching minor flood, the river at Geneva is forecast to crest around 8.2 feet by this weekend.
For the St. Johns River...including Above Lake Harney...Minor flooding is forecast.
Additional information is available at www.weather.gov.
The next statement will be issued this evening at 1100 PM EDT.
* WHAT...Minor flooding is forecast.
* WHERE...St Johns River near Above Lake Harney.
* WHEN...From late tonight until further notice.
* IMPACTS...At 8.3 feet, Docks are partially submerged along the river between Lake Harney and Lemon Bluff.
* ADDITIONAL DETAILS... - At 9:30 AM EDT Tuesday the stage was 7.8 feet. - Bankfull stage is 6.0 feet. - Forecast...The river is expected to rise above flood stage just after midnight tonight and continue rising to 8.2 feet early Thursday morning. Additional rises are possible thereafter. - Flood stage is 8.0 feet. - http://www.weather.gov/safety/flood

parameter.value: FLOOD WARNING NOW IN EFFECT FROM LATE TONIGHT UNTIL FURTHER NOTICE
